{
  "texts": [
    "Several studies [14,52] evaluate different table serialization formats to assess whether LLMs accurately understand structured tables.",
    "They compare formats like CSV, markdown, JSON, HTML and pandas DataFrame.",
    "The evaluation results suggest that HTML and NL with separators (markdown or CSV) are the two most effective options, which can be assumed that the training corpora include substantial code and Web tables.",
    "Spreadsheets may contain merged cells and hierarchical columns, meaning simple row-by-row and column-by-column serialization is insufficient.",
    "Tian et al. [53] argue that homogeneous rows or columns in spreadsheets contribute little to understanding their layout and structure."
  ]
}